Introduction of Estonian folk music through its functions as musical mother tongue. Analysis of folk music collection, research, expression and popularization as different periodical strata constituting parts of general cultural lore. The historical background of major Estonian folk instruments, their development and usage. Contemporary use and styles of folk music in Estonia and elsewhere.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Provide an overview of the historical strata and functions of Estonian folk music as musical mother tongue, and analyze the strata against a variety of backgrounds.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Knows, how musical traditions work and is able to find them in surrounding cultural environment.
Knows the musical instruments that have been traditionally used in Estonian areas.
Knows the most important publications and sources concerning Estonian traditional music.
